    Bone marrow lesions and MRI-detected structural abnormalities in people with midfoot pain and osteoarthritis: a cross-sectional study.
 In people with persistent midfoot pain but no x-ray signs of OA, MRI findings suggested an under-recognised prevalence of OA, particularly in the 2 nd and 3 rd cuneiform-metatarsal joints, where BML patterns were consistent with previously recognised sites of elevated mechanical loading. Joint abnormalities were not strongly associated with pain or foot-related disability.
