The SUMO components in rheumatoid arthritis.
In addition, single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) in the SUMO components have been reported to be associated with disease susceptibility. Until now, only the SNP site of SUMO-4 has been reported in RA. Here we provided a systematic overview of the general characteristics of SUMO components and highlighted a summary of their impact on RA.
